body:
Hi,

Please excuse me for getting back to you that late!

@asdluki I wasn't able yet to reproduce this issue with your diff_response.txt file. In my tests, the parser is able to parse this file. It doesn't contain a "\ No Newline at End of File". Although I have a rule for the no newline case in the parser, it could be that it fails in certain scenarios. Is it often the case that the parser is not able to handle your pull requests? Could you please give me another example where the parser failed due to the no newline issue? That would be very helpful!

@wiseeker Could you please provide me a diff as explained above for a pull request where the plug-in fails? That would be very helpful!

Hi,

thanks a lot for the examples.

@tajain I was able to fix this issue. It was caused by the fact that apparently a line like
\ No newline at end of file
can appear at any position not just at the end of a file diff. Do you mind if I use your example as a test case which would mean that it will be part of this Github repository?

@asdluki My parser now runs all 3 of your examples after the mentioned fix. Do you mind if I use diff_wrong1.txt and diff_wrong3.txt as test cases which would mean that they will be part of this Github repository?
